## A brief overview ##

Dux is a new and constantly changing [Operating System](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operating_system) with goals to have a simple overall design, be easy to port to new architectures, and easy to create new software for. It uses the equally new and changing [metodo kernel](/dux/metodo).
Although it is designed to be portable, at the moment it only runs on [x86](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/x86) systems.
The dux project began in late 2008 as an experiment which soon became a regular project over the next few months.
As time went on, more people joined and several revisions of dux were created, leaving a clean and well designed core that will be both fast and extendable.

## What's with the name? ##
I was given the nickname duck, courtesy of my friend Ashley, my sophomore year of highschool.  Over time pretty much everybody I know started calling me duck.  When I asked a friend what I should call my Operating System, she said "dux."

I'm assuming they're related.

